   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER ONE THE ISSUE OF GOD'S IMPARTATION</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND TRANSMISSION IN HIS DIVINE TRINITY</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>INTO HIS CHOSEN PEOPLE, AS THE CHURCH,</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>THE FULLNESS OF THE ONE</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>WHO FILLS ALL IN ALL Scripture Reading: Eph 1:3-6, 7-12, 13-14, 18-23 OUTLINE The issue of God the Father's impartation: Of His holy nature into His chosen people that they may be separated from the world and sanctified wholly unto Him Eph 1:4.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Of His divine life into His predestinated people that they may become His many sons for His expression v. 5.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To the praise of the glory expression of His grace v. 6.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The issue of God the Son's impartation of the divine element into God the Father's chosen and predestinated people: In the redemption through His blood v. 7.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To bring them into Christ as their sphere and element, that they may be made God's inheritance, with the divine element in Christ, as a treasure to God vv.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>8-11.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>To the praise of God the Father's glory expression in the believers who have first hoped in Christ v. 12.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The issue of God the Spirit's impartation of the divine essence into God the Father's inheritance redeemed by God the Son: By sealing it God's inheritance that it may be saturated with the divine essence as the impress to be a mark and the image of God to be His expression v. 13.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>By being a pledge of God as His redeemed people's inheritance for their foretaste of Him, guaranteeing their full taste of Him, unto the redemption of His acquired possession redeemed inheritance v. 14a.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>To the praise of God's glory expression v. 14b.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The issue of the transmission of God in His divine trinity into His chosen and redeemed people: As the great power toward the believers, which God caused to operate in Christ: In raising Him from the dead.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>In seating Him at the Father's right hand in the heavenlies, far above all.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>In subjecting all things under His feet.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>In giving Him to be the Head over all things.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>As the transmission to the church, which is the Body of Christ, the One who fills all in all vv.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>19-23.</S>
   </TEXT>
